{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4fc50f03-cfc4-43ab-97c5-26426bd3d4df","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android =>\n    {\n        android.OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ });\n        android.OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ });\n    });\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios =>\n    {\n        ios.DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ });\n    });\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Use **preprocessor directives** (`#if ANDROID`, `#elif IOS`) to keep platform code conditional.\n- The `AddAndroid` / `AddiOS` extension methods expose the native lifecycle callbacks directly.\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` for the extension methods.\n- Available NuGet: these APIs are built into `Microsoft.Maui.Essentials` (included by default).\n\nFor a **cross-platform** alternative, subscribe to `App.Current.Windows[0].Deactivated` or override `OnSleep()` in your `App.xaml.cs` — though these are less granular than the platform-specific hooks above.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8c76b95-e2ef-46ea-a720-24f06fcd315e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":413,"requestId":"B7CE:3611D2:13A0B7:19BC1E:69FFD82C"},"id":"0e005167-36ad-4f2b-96a4-bbe7fe30a925","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:58:28.653Z","parentId":"48380118-866c-45d1-90b0-4480063f4f88"}
